 Dear WillI'm sorry it has taken us so long to reply. But we're going to do=
 as much as we can this weekend.
First, regarding the image banner, we like the first one, with its suggesti=
on of the Malvern Hills.
Although Lynne wondered whether the colour scheme - at least for the "waves=
" - could be some shade of green, we think perhaps we could save colour hig=
hlights for some future time (e.g. Xmas)
Regarding the sections,=C2=A0 I don't think we need=C2=A0'Join us' or =E2=
=80=98education' and I assume that =E2=80=98news' would be covered within=
=C2=A0home, events or "about".
We're currently looking through the photos taken by Michael Whitefoot, the =
professional photographer last year. Some are "group" photos (or subgroups)=
. There are also individual photos of Lynne and the choir members. We plan =
to send you them, with some notes that could be used to caption them.
I will send you the poster for the coming concert, and from it=C2=A0 i'll s=
end you the text for the ticket website, and the image of the QR code that =
points to it, and also a list of future concerts
Then the main thing for us to do is send you the copy you've asked for, whi=
ch we will do pronto.
Thank you so much.Best wishesMalcolm=C2=A0
    On Saturday, 31 January 2026 at 18:43:11 GMT, Will Kirby <williamgkirby=
@gmail.com> wrote: =20
=20
 Hello Lynne & Malcolm,
I have started on the site, and have a few questions please.  =20
   - Copy
   - Look / Feel
