ilar? I can use this for the =E2=80=98about=E2=80=99 / =E2=80=98history=E2=
=80=99 sections.
Look / feel.=C2=A0I have begun to mess about with designs / themes - but I=
=E2=80=99m also keen for you to take the lead on the visuals. Are there any=
 websites you rate highly? It doesn=E2=80=99t matter if they are for cars /=
 companies / whatever; rather than music related. I=E2=80=99m keen to get a=
 colour scheme and / or =E2=80=98feel=E2=80=99 (modern vs. trad, clean vs v=
aried etc).
=C2=A0Some initial ideas from me to show the kind of thing which is possibl=
e are below. I haven=E2=80=99t focussed on the finer text and / or graphic =
design - i=E2=80=99m just trying to get a sense of your taste and preferenc=
es:
https://williamgki.github.io/jls-website/index_waves_final.html=C2=A0- i th=
ough the waves are a bit like sound waves, but also the malvern hillshttps:=
//williamgki.github.io/jls-website/index_botanical.html=C2=A0- botanical, s=
imilar theme to the logo
https://williamgki.github.io/jls-website/index_nordic.html=C2=A0- a variant=
 on the waves, but using more of the logo.

Sections:I looked through some of the sites you mentioned, and others from =
Bryony to see what they contain and have pasted the section titles below. I=
n the drafts above i settled on: home, events & tickets, about the choir, l=
isten, our ethos and support. let me know if you=E2=80=99d like more? 'Join=
 us', =E2=80=98education', =E2=80=98news' are all options.=C2=A0
